Hello,

We have not heard back from you since you posted the issue. Not sure if this is still throwing error in your app. We tested this issue the test code below. It displays similar to displaying content on web browser. Not sure if you are experiencing the same in your app. If so, please send us a test case so that we can take next necessary step to fix. If we don't hear back, we will assume the issue is no longer valid and close it.  

h5. Test Environment

OS: MAC OS X 10.8.5
Ti SDK: 3.2.0.x
Ti CLI: 3.3.0
IOS simulator   7.0
h5. Test Code
{code}
 
var win = Ti.UI.createWindow({
	backgroundColor : '#fff',
	exitOnClose : true,
	fullscreen : false,
	layout : 'vertical',
	title : 'Color Demo'
});

var aWebView = Ti.UI.createWebView({
	url : 'http://www.reachlite.com'
});
aWebView.addEventListener('load', function(e) {
	Ti.API.info('webview loaded: ' + e.url);
});

win.add(aWebView);

win.open();
{code}



h5. Step to reproduces
# Create a new project
# Paste test code in app.js
# Now run on iOS simulator


h5. Test Result

Website will be loaded perfectly in Webview.

Thanks
